title: ci: add migrations workflow
body:
### Description

We have already had some conflicts due to working with migrations in parallel. To solve this problem, I have created a workflow that updates the migrations, resolves any possible conflicts and creates a new migration if necessary each time a push to develop or a pr to develop or main is performed.

### Additional context

Results of this action

In `PRs`: Resolves conflicts and generates migrations automatically, ensuring that changes are ready before merging.
In `push`: As a backup, ensures that any migrations that were not resolved in a PR are automatically handled when doing a direct push.

This way conflicts are resolved early in the workflow (in PRs), but any undetected issues are fixed when pushing to develop.

body:
### Description

Added unit, Selenium, and Locust tests for WI1-SearchQueries.

### Additional context

Unit tests:
- test_zip_with_valid_models_ids: Downloads the correct models selected.
- test_generate_zip_filename: Creates the zip file name and adds it to the download correctly.
- test_invalid_file_ids: Prevents downloading the zip if there is an invalid model ID.
- test_generate_zip_with_empty_file_ids: Prevents downloading the zip if there are no model IDs.
- test_generate_zip_with_unexisting_file_ids: Prevents downloading the zip if there is a nonexistent model ID.
- test_generate_zip_with_mixed_valid_and_invalid_file_ids: Prevents downloading the zip if there are invalid model IDs.

Interface tests (selenium):
- TestDownloadselected1: Tests downloading a single selected file in a dataset.
- TestDownloadselected2: Tests downloading two different selected files in a dataset.
- TestDownloadselected0: Tests downloading no files.

Load test (locust):
- download_selected: Tests the system's capacity to handle 10 different users downloading selected files.
